observationText: Heterozygous Nf1GRD/+ mice appeared normal and were able to breed, but heterozygous intercrosses failed to produce any viable homozygous Nf1GRD/GRD pups, indicating that the homozygous R1276P mutation of Nf1 causes midgestation embryonic lethality with most embryos succumbing by E12.5.
